{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/tws-ios.TWS\/tutorials\/TWS\/Notifications","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[{"kind":"hero","estimatedTimeInMinutes":3,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this tutorial you will learn how to easily integrate TWSNotifications in your existing push notification code base.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"chapter":"Display your first snippet","title":"Integrating TWSNotifications with your notifications"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"title":"Integrating TWSNotifications","anchor":"Integrating-TWSNotifications","stepsSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Integration of TWSNotifications is very easy. Wherever your app receives a notification, just pass the data to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handleTWSPushNotification(userInfo:) method like so."}]}],"caption":[{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By the time notification is processed by this method, the TWSManager holding the snippet should already be alive."}]}]}],"media":null,"code":"Notifications_00.swift","runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notification data should include two keys “type” and “path”. If they are not include handleTWSPushNotification(userInfo:) will ignore the notification."}]}],"caption":[{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"projectId and snippetId should be replaced with actual ids, again this will work correctly if the TWSManager with the same projectId configuration already exists."}]}]}],"media":null,"code":"Notifications.json","runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As noted in first step TWSManager needs to be alive when push notification is handled. This usually means that the instance s